http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/telangana/KU-prof.-to-deliver-talk-at-science-congress/article13978147.ece

Prof. P. Malla Reddy of Mathematics Department was invited to deliver a talk at the 103rd Indian Science Congress scheduled from January 3 to 7 in Mysore University. He would deliver a lecture on “Biot’s extension theory of porous materials”. This year Mysore University is hosting the mega event and the theme titled, Science and technology for indigenous development in India. It would be inaugurated by Prime Minister Narendra Modi. Scientists from India and abroad would participate in the congress. Invited speakers include Nobel laureates, Bharat Ratna, Padmabhushan awardees, and officials from the Ministry of Science and Technology. Apart from plenary talks, there would be invited talks and paper presentations in fourteen domains of science, medicine, and engineering.